snippet.textDisplay: How do you then explain Chael him taking down Conor and Al Iaquinta in basically the center of the Octagon?? And with Conor, he was on the back foot, which is even harder. I think that guy is so good and unstoppable, he shoots so fast and it doesn't really matter if he is in the open or got you on the fence. Yes, we can all see and acknowledge that he does his best work when he pushes his opponent's back against the fence, him and his father perfected that style of wrestling for YEARS which is the most suitable for MMA, but he shoots so fast and is faster than anyone trying to defend from being taken down by him. Conor might've survived and the fight might've gone a little different if he didn't throw that knee on Khabib's entry, which helped Khabib take him down eventually. As someone says, Khabib only needs your pinky toe to cling on to you. It's ridiculous. He may be a little less effective when in the open space and in that center of the Octagon as you point out Chael. But man oh man, he will take you down no matter what. It's really interesting the level of skill and determination that guy has. Never seen anything like it in the sport of MMA. Him and Jones are for me the greatest fighters ever, because Jon has so many tools and is so calm, has such an unwavering winner's mentality, and Khabib is just mentally bulletproof and determined as nobody else is + grappling prowess which have been honed and sharpen since the age of 3. IMO, if he beats Tony, I really can't see anyone beating him. Justin Gaethje has got a good style and styles make fights but Khabib IMO has basically a better cardio and a better work rate. And wrestling is not the same as grappling all in all. If they end up on the ground, which they most likely will - Khabib will pass guard and start to throw bombs and destroy Justin.
